TITLE: Exposing Java Methods with Callback Arguments
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to expose Java methods that accept or return callback functions using @JsFunction. It includes a functional interface and static methods that work with it.
SOURCE: https://github.com/gwtproject/gwt-site/blob/main/src/main/markdown/doc/latest/DevGuideCodingBasicsJsInterop.md#2025-04-09_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
package com.example;

@JsType
public class Bar {
    @JsFunction
    public interface Foo {
        int exec(int x);
    }

    public static int action1(Foo foo) {
        return foo.exec(40);
